The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, April 11, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Mumbai, April 10: Indias foreign exchange reserves surged ahead in the first week of the new fiscal following fresh accretion of over $1 billion to move past the record levels of $112 billion during the week ending April 2, 2004. Market purchases by the RBI revaluation of the dollar vis-a-vis other currencies, export remittances and fresh inflows led to inflows of $1,068 million enabling forex reserves to climb to $1,12,680 million.																								 Mumbai, April 10: India could see resolution of non-performing loans (NPL) worth $3-5 billion (gross value of loans) over the next 12-18 months, Ernst amp; Young, the international management consultant, said today. The resolution process is expected to be led by the Asset Reconstruction Company (India) Ltd and other ARCs being set up in India, E amp;Y said in its report on Global NPLs 2004 here today.																								 Mumbai, April 10: The Reserve Bank of India will conduct an auction of two government treasury bills totalling Rs 4,000 crore, including Rs 2,500 crore under the market stabilisation scheme (MSS), on April 13. 
